programme.desc: Captains Tom Rowland and Rich Tudor are joined by scientist Nick Haddad, who educates the hosts and the fishing world on the various descending devices used to preserve stressed catch from deeper waters.

programme.title: Hunting Land Man
programme.desc: The 2024 turkey season has arrived. Slade and Bentley are already off to a great start. Bentley managed to take one down during opening weekend for youth hunt and Slade takes one down opening day.

programme.title: Local Knowledge
programme.desc: Ali and Rush head to the Bay Flats Lodge in Seadrift, Texas, to fish the vast shallow water marshes of the San Antonio Bay for redfish.

programme.title: Flavor on the Fly
programme.sub-title: Vermont - Northern Pike, Backcountry Brook Trout, and Mushroom Foraging
programme.desc: Welcome to Flavor on the Fly In the first installment of our newest original series, Chef Ranga Perera trades the towering Rockies for the rolling hills in the Green Mountain State. Out of his element and on a mission to find .

programme.title: Destination Dive
programme.desc: Off Key West lives an impressive shipwreck; traveling to Big Pine Key, home to spectacular reefs, including Looe Key.

programme.title: Huckberry Homes
programme.sub-title: How This Photographer Manifested His Dream Home on the Oregon Coast
programme.desc: Tired of fixing up other people's houses, Ben decided to spend the last few years crafting his own house from the ground up, while getting help from his friends, Dad, and Sophie along the way.

programme.title: Hard Truths Of Conservation
programme.desc: Join Dan Cabela in New Zealand's breathtaking landscapes as he hunts non-native species, delving into the crucial role of controlled harvesting and the complexities of managing introduced wildlife.

programme.title: The Green Way Outdoors
programme.desc: Kyle and Jeff explore the oceans off the coast of Hawaii; they encounter sharks, manta rays and even jump off a 40-foot cliff.

programme.title: Dean Partridge's Canadian Whitetail
programme.desc: A giant 200 whitetail and two friends hunting him miles apart; the time is ticking for one to find success.

programme.title: Stomping Grounds
programme.sub-title: Lone Star Boating: Exploring Central Texas Lakes & Rivers
programme.desc: The Boat Trader heads to central Texas to explore boating culture in Texas, known as the place where everything is bigger; the state is about more than big oil, college football and cattle farms: it's also home to the best boating in the country.

programme.title: Ship Shape TV
programme.sub-title: Ship Shape TV Essentials -- Rub Rail Restoration & DIY Paint Bucket
programme.desc: Tips for making improvements and repairs on boats and boat equipment.

programme.title: Goin' Coastal
programme.desc: Showcases Captain Josh and Sheriff Eric Aden for a day of fishing and fun in Destin, Fla.; the two friends hit the water, catching fish both offshore and inshore, and reeling in some impressive catches.

programme.title: Winchester Life
programme.desc: Charles Rodney's relationship with his hunting dogs and connection to the land make his love for chasing rabbits contagious; a Model 42 collection for the ages and hunting Kansas coyotes with the Keefer brothers.
